
void room_message(object *aoPeople, object oRoom, string sMessage)

Similar to tell_room(), but allows variable text depending on who is receiving
the message. The message string is in the same format as general emotes,
although this usage cannot handle passing non-living objects, and does not allow
special cases separated by ||. The composed message sMessage is spammed to
the room oRoom, with the array aoPeople being the array of people involved in
the message.

